I'm sorry, but if I see &quot;plz&quot; &quot;u&quot; &quot;ne 1&quot; &quot;SoW&quot; &quot;thx&quot; or any other abbreviation in there for a buff or word in your request, it's an automatic no.  If you can't take the time to type out your request politely, I don't have the time to help you.  I'm not asking for people to make huge requests like..  &quot;Please fair druid, could you grant me the spirit of wolf so that I might get my corpse?&quot;..  all I'd like to see is, &quot;Could you give me spirit of wolf please&quot; and it's as good as done.  If you make the request a command (i.e. sow me) you just hit my ignore list and you'll be there until I forget why I put you there.  <br>
<br>
I've done GG's and Buffs for free LOTS of times.. hell when I was lvl 39 and just got my new spells I went to G-fay and spent an entire week on &quot;orc hill&quot; buffing and healing people..gating people that wanted it.  It isn't like I'm some heartless bugger, but if you're asking me to be polite and nice in giving you a buff, I expect the request to be equally nice and polite.  <br>
<br>
