 What gets a little annoying is when people send you a tell for those things, and you find out that they are a few zones away! O__o Or when you land at a druid ring on your way to join a group, or to pick up group members, and people are actually camping the ring. &quot;buffs plz&quot; &quot;thorn me, I need to break the orc camp&quot; &quot;can you port me? why not, can't you just bind here and port back?&quot;<br>
 I've even had people complain when I gave them chloro and skin like diamond, (the efffects on es bp and legs, to save mana and the memming of spells of course!)because they wanted skin like nature, or natureskin which won't even take hold on them due to thier lvl. That to me seems a little ungrateful and can be a little annoying. <br>
I can understand some druids getting a little snappy when they get asked for a port or buffs every time they zone. I usually give what I think is a polite response if I am busy. But I have to say, I am never too busy for the giving of a simple sow. Personally, I always have it memmed. The only times I wouldn't give a sow is if I am asked for it rudely, or if the person is not even in the zone. ;)  <br>
<br>
Leiaa Lookingwolf<br>
