/24/01 6:06:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sow/buff/port requests</span><hr size=1> Tuven, I agree totally and do the same, except the ignore list, I reserve that for particularly annoying people.<br>
<br>
A good friend of mine, he's a wizzie, loves clarity, and he generally pays for it if he have to, 5-10 plats, and he always offers to pay if he sends a tell directly to the chanter.<br>
<br>
Personally, it's nice to have, but I can do without. My point is, sow costs what? 40 mana, well, Clarity costs 35 mana, and people are a lot more willing to pay for that than to pay for sow. Or a rez, I almost always give 50pp's for it if I can afford it, it costs them 700 mana, if I recall correctly, a port costs us 300 mana, and we are forced to zone twice, maybe bind and gate and later move our bind point back where we wanted it, which, all in all costs me a lot more time than what it costs the cleric doing the rez.<br>
<br>
Yet, our spells, or services if you will, are unappreciated and expected to be given at no or low cost to anyone who asks. To me, the more polite a person is, the more likely they are to get what they want, and maybe a few extra buffs before they leave. If I get a rez, I always SoW the cleric afterwards, if I do buy or get a clarity, SoW for the chanter, and<br>
if I got it up or are not in a hurry, SLN.<br>
<br>
While you think about this, all I want are politeness, I don't care about cash, I always refuse cash for SoW, the people who offer cash are the people I want to SoW anyway.<br>
<br>
Ports are a little different, but I generally decline cash offered nowadays, that is, unless I'm doing it for the cash. If I'm heading to the same zone as someone, or they have been shouting for a port for a while and appear to be polite, I will offer to port them for free.<br>
<br>
But in the end, it is my time, it is my mana, it is up to me to decide what to do with it.<br>
<br>
Glarnor Wandenbaum &lt;Wind Guardians&gt;<br>
